review_blob: Clear golden amber body and a rocky white head. First a nice hop aroma of pine and citrus, then caramel and heavy spiced from the rosemary. The taste is medium sweet and medium to heavy bitter. Oily texture and medium carbonation.

Black hazy body and a dark brown hazy head. Nice creamy "micro brew" texture. Aroma of espresso coffee, dark chocolate. Lots of taste. A really well balanced taste. Heavy sweet and very light bitterness.
Draught at Fa!rBar. Strange taste with a mix of coffee and hops, but it doesnt work together. Ends up with a taste of bitter-swet the.
beer_name: Flying Couch Hops And Coffee Drops

review_blob: Draught at Fa!rBar. Black body and a small creamy head. Aroma of coffee and bitter hops. Has a long bitter finish.

Bottle at Jelling Kro. Hazy brown body and off-white creamy head. Nice aroma of chocolate, caramel and coffee. The taste is medium to heavy sweet and light to medium bitter. Well balanced and not acid or sour like the previous ratings says. Creamy texture and medium body.
Dark brown body and a small off-white head. Aroma of caramel, roasted malt, raisin. The taste is heavy sweet and medium bitter. Thick, sticky body. Powerfull but easy to drink.
Draught at Fermentoren, Aarhus. Pink cloudy body and a white-pink rocky head. Aroma og cherries, basement aromas, sour milk. The taste is heavy sweet and light milk sour.

Draught at Mikkellerbar, Aarhus. Amber clear body and a small diminishing rocky head. Heavy aroma of smoke, some vanilla and caramel. The taste is medium sweet and light bitter. Long smoke finish, oily texture.
Draught at Fa!rBar, Aarhus. Yellow body and a white rocky head. Nice hops aroma of citrus and pine. Well balanced taste medium sweet and medium to heavy bitter. Nice !
Draught at Fa!rBar, Aarhus. Golden hazy body and a small rocky head. Fruity and Yeasty aroma of apricot, pine and spices. Medium sweet and bitter with a long bitter finish. Heavy alcohol
Black hazy body and a dark brown creamy head. Nice aroma of chocolate, coffee. full body, soft carbonation. Well balanced heavy sweet and medium bitter. A Nice beer without any surprices.
Hazy golden body and a small white head. Aroma of wheat, citrus and yeast. The taste is medium sweet, light bitter and sour.

beer_brewer_name: Josef Schneiders Kleines Brauhaus im Altmhltal
review_blob: Bottle from Greifenklau, Bamberg. Black body and a brown creamy head that lasts for a short time. Nice aroma of coffee, chocolate and dark caramel. Fresh hop finish. The taste is well balanced medium to heavy sweet and medium bitter. Sticky texture. Nice beer !
Clear golden body and a rocky white head. Aroma of citrus, honey, pine and grass. The taste is medium sweet and medium to heavy bitter with a long well balanced honey bitter finish. Thin body.

Cloudy light yellow-white body and a large lasting white creamy head. Aroma much like a belgian wit - just more strong in alcohol Wheat, citrus and lots of spices. The taste is light to medium sweet and medium bitter with a long bitter finish. Light body.
Draft at Mikkeller, Aarhus. Orange body, small fastly diminishing head. Aroma of apricot and wood. Fruity, the taste is heavily sour.
Draft at Mikkeller, Aarhus. Dark brow body and a small white creamy head. Aroma of coffee, chocolate and roasted malt.
Draft at Mikkelbar, Aarhus. Fruity and yeasty. Hazy light yellow body. The taste is medium sweet and with a well balanced bitter finish.
Dark brown hazy body and a off-white rocky head. Aroma of roasted malt, chocolate, oranges. The taste is medium to heavy sweet and medium bitter. Full body, creamy texture.
Hazy golden body and a white creamy head. Aroma of honey, coriander, caramel, bread and citrus. Well balanced medium sweet and bitter. Dry hop finish.
Cloudy light yellow-white body and a rocky white head. Aroma of wheat, spices, citrus. The taste is medium sweet and very light bitter. Thin body. Refreshing.
Bottle bought at Klosterbru, Bamberg. Golden orange hazy body and a white creamy head. Aroma of banana, hay, bread, yeast. Medium sweet and light bitter.

beer_brewer_name: Josef Schneiders Kleines Brauhaus im Altmhltal
review_blob: Bottle from Greifenklau in Bamberg. Hazy orange golden body and a large creamy lasting head. Aroma of bread, caramel, honey, apricot, flowers. Rater sweet taste and good balanced hop taste. Creamy texture and a soft carbonation.
Hazy golden body and a small rocky diminishing head. Rather sweet beer with aroma of honey, coriander, alcohol. The taste is medium to heavy sweet and light bitter.
Clear dark brown body and a off-white lasting creamy head.Sweet aroma of dried fruits, brown sugar, roasted malt. Sweet taste and Sticky texture.
Tap at Mikkeller Bar, Aarhus. Hazy light orange body and a small rocky head. Aroma of basement, vinegar, abricot, malt. The taste has a medium sourness, but still well balanced. Nice refreshing.

Tap at Zunfststube in Kulmbach. Hazy golden light brown body and a large white lasting rocky head. Aroma of malt, Yeasty. The taste is well balanced medium sweet and light to medium bitter. Creamy texture and low carbonation.
On tap at the brewery museum 07/11/15. Hazy amber body and a large lasting creamy head. Aroma of caramel, yeast, hay. Medium sweet and light to medium bitter. Thin feel. Nothing special.
Tap at Kommunbru 07/11/2015. Hazy light brown body and a large white creamy head. Aroma of caramel, nuts, light roasted malt. Refreshing taste medium sweet and bitter. Thin body and easy to drink.

Tap at Kommunbru 07/11/2015. Nice hazy amber-orange body and a large creamy head. Aroma of lots of malt, apricot, yeast and alcohol. The taste is well balanced, medium to heavy sweet and medium bitter. Thick and creamy texture. Nice!
Clear brown body and a small off-white head. Aroma of roasted malt and lots of sweet vanilla. Im not sure, that it is doing any good. Medium to heavy sweet and light to medium bitter. Sticky texture.
Clear amber brown body and a small head. Aroma of caramel, nuts, roasty, alcohol. Medium to heavy sweet and light to medium bitter. Long bitter finish - to long.
Draught at Greifenklau. Hazy amber brown body and a small rocky head. Aroma of caramel, yeasty and som fine hops. Well balanced taste medium sweet and light to medium bitter. Oily texture.

Clear brown body and aa nive off-white lasting creamy head. Aroma og caramel, brown sugar, nuts. The taste is medium to heavy sweet and medium bitter. Sticky texture, medium body, average carbonation.
Cloudy golde body and a small white rocky head. Yeasty, citrus, hay and cereal. Medium sweet and light bitter. Slightly sour. Medium body.
Golden hazy body and large creamy white head. Aroma of cereal, hay, citrus but no banana. Nice. The taste is medium sweet and light bitter. Oily texture and medium body.
Bottle at Mahr Bru. Amber hazy body and a large creamy head. Aroma of malt, hay, yeast and banana. Medium sweet and light bitter. Medium body, oily feel, average carbonation. Nice and refreshing.
Draught at Keesmann, Bamberg. Golden clear body and a white rocky head. Aroma of malt, light fruity and some alcohol. The taste is medium sweet and bitter.

Draught at Keesmann, Bamberg. Dark golde hazy bodt and a large white creamy head. Aroma of cereal, bread, light banana. The taste is medium sweet and light bitter. Creamy texture. A nice refreshing beer.
Draught at Spezial. Brown body and rocky white head. Lovely aroma of smoke, roasted malt, caramel. The taste is medium sweet and light to medium bitter.
Clear golden body and a small diminishing white head. The taste is medium sweet. Aroma of herbs, alcohol, caramel, floral. Medium body, sticky texture.
Cloudy light yellow body and a small fastly diminishing white rocky head. Aroma of cereal, toast, yeast, flowers and soap. Medium sweet and light bitter. Mild. Light body, thin feel, flat.
Clear golden body and a white rocky head with good lacing. Sweet aroma og herbs, honey and bread. The taste is medium to heavy sweet and medium bitter. Oily and some sticky texture

Draft at Michaelsberg Cafe. Clear dark brown body and a creamy white head. Aroma of caramel and roasted malt. The taste is medium to heavy sweet and light to medium bitter. Sticky texture. Nice and warming.
Golden clear body and a white rocky head. Aroma of hay, cereal, alcohol, floral. The taste is medium sweet and bitter, long bitter finish.
Black body and a small white diminishing head. Aroma of roasted malt and lots of licorice. The taste is heavy sweet and light bitter. Thin body.
Thick dark body and a dark brown lasting head. Aroma of chocolate, coffee, nuts, port wine, dried red fruits. The taste is heavy sweet and light to medium bitter. Thick sticky body.
beer_name: De Molen / Hof ten Dormaal Vallen & Opstaan

review_blob: Draught at fa!rbar Aarhus. Thick black body and a brown head. Heavy aroma of roasted malt and citrus, grass and pine. Medium to heavy sweetness and heavy bitter. Long bitter finish. To heavy and bitter in my opinion.
Draght at Fa!rBar Aarhus. Hazy dark brown body and a large off-white head. Nice aroma of smoke, malty aroma. Really well balanced. The taste is medium sweet and light bitter
Clear brown body and a small off-white creamy head. Aroma of brown sugar, nuts, licorice and some hops in the finish. Heavy sweet and light bitter taste. Sticky texture.
